CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1958, pg. 17 reads: " "Miss Fairview" - Joyce Sharpe, representing Wesley Center AME Zion Church, won the title "Miss Fairview" in the contest sponsored by the Monongahela Valley Sunday School Association which closed with the recent May Festival. Norma Jean Coughman, left, representing Park Place AME, placed second; Rodman Street's representative, Arzinia Hendricks, right, won third-place honors.  Last year's winner, Shirley Standford, crowned the new "queen." - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Joyce Sharpe who won the title "Miss Fairview," seated in front of, from left: Norma Jean Coughman, last year's winner Shirley Standford, and Arzinia Hendricks
